In [5]:
# Our spaCy model:
nlp = en_core_web_md.load()
# Tags I want to remove from the text
removal= ['ADV','PRON','CCONJ','PUNCT','PART','DET','ADP','SPACE',
'NUM', 'SYM']
tokens = []
for summary in nlp.pipe(df['Resume']):
    proj_tok = [token.lemma_.lower() for token in summary if
token.pos_ not in removal and not token.is_stop and token.is_alpha]
    tokens.append(proj_tok)
In [6]:
df["tokens"] = tokens

Calculating the coherence score using C_umass:¶

In [11]:
topics = []
score = []
for i in range(1,20,1):
    lda_model = LdaMulticore(corpus=corpus, id2word=dictionary, iterations=10, num_topics=i, workers = 4, passes=10, random_state=100)
    cm = CoherenceModel(model=lda_model, corpus=corpus, dictionary=dictionary, coherence='u_mass')
    topics.append(i)
    score.append(cm.get_coherence())
_=plt.plot(topics, score)
_=plt.xlabel('Number of Topics')
_=plt.ylabel('Coherence Score')
plt.show()

Calculating the coherence score using C_v:¶

In [12]:
topics = []
score = []

for i in range(1,20,1):
    lda_model = LdaMulticore(corpus=corpus, id2word=dictionary, iterations=10, num_topics=i, workers = 4, passes=10, random_state=100)
    cm = CoherenceModel(model=lda_model, texts = df['tokens'], corpus=corpus, dictionary=dictionary, coherence='c_v')

    topics.append(i)
    score.append(cm.get_coherence())
_=plt.plot(topics, score)
_=plt.xlabel('Number of Topics')
_=plt.ylabel('Coherence Score')
plt.show()

The C_v score above 0.5 is termed good so the optimum number of topics is 18.

Conclusion¶

As we can see from the interactive graph, this process doesn't create good enough clusters to be used properly as a functional job classifier. In our next attempt, we would proceed to train our model by applying custom rules for job classification using spaCy's Named-entity recognition tool called EntityRecognizer.
